          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1686046381015-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>diced tomato</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>remaining red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>remaining harissa paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) and cook for 2-3 min or until the tomato starts to break down</p><p>Add 2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tsp]</span><strong> sugar </strong>with<strong> </strong>100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[130ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[150ml]</span><strong> cold water</strong>, then cook for 6-8 min further, stirring frequently, or until thickened and sticky – this is your<strong> spiced tomato sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686046381332-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686046381332-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1686046381332-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
